      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MEHSUN (5) imported gelding who made his Australian debut with a narrow fifth over 1550m. Will improve as he gets out further in trip and gets map favours today. Ready to win. NUCLEAR PETE (6) savaged the line last on the turn when he made his debut with a close-up third over 1200m at Gosford. Fitter now and has the key jockey change for this. Look for him motoring late. ADENAUER (1) not that far away on resumption with a tidy fifth over 1250m at Canterbury in a Super Maiden. Desperate to get out over a bit of ground and the winkers go on. Top-three player. ARTGIRL (9) handy filly who should shed her Maiden tag quickly this time in. Found the 1100m too short first-up with a plugging third in the small field over 1100m here. Ready for this trip and stays in the mix.",
